The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | Hospital in expand mode
                                                                                                                         3                                                                                      Hospital in expand mode
          A STAFF REPORTER                              
	Belle Vue Clinic plans to launch facilities and upgrade existing ones spending Rs 45 crore. The blueprint includes setting up of cardiology and mother and child care units, a blood bank and a nursing college in Behala and procurement of modern equipment.         
	The cardiology and mother and child care units will be housed in a new building in our Minto Park property and commissioned in October, said P. Tandon, the CEO of Belle Vue Clinic.        
	The mother and child care unit will have 70 beds and the cardiology wing 22 intensive therapy unit (ITU) beds, taking Belle Vues total bed count to 304. We will conduct cardiac surgery, angioplasty and other invasive and non-invasive procedures, said Tandon.         
	The hospitals blood bank, which currently stores only whole blood, will also store platelets, fresh frozen plasma, concentrated red blood cells.         
	On Saturday, the hospital installed a high capacity biochemistry analyser  DXC 600  that will make blood analysis easier and faster. The equipment, which was installed at a cost of Rs 80 lakh, can conduct 65 types of chemical tests with one blood sample, said Tirthankar Dhar of the pathology department.         
	Belle Vue is also planning to introduce a biopsy machine with advanced tissue typing facility. The nursing college will be ready in two years, said Tandon. There is a 30-acre plot in Behala, part of which will be used for the nursing college, he added.                                                                                                                                                           
